731131f-b.title: Celebrations - Parades - Municipal Events - Army Day Parade.
731131f-b.text:
Celebrations, Parades and Municipal Events A set of three views of whct the writer believes to be an Army Day Parade, being reviewed from a stand at the Arsenal in Central Park. View No. 1 shows the marchers passing the dfgnitaries which include General Pershing (shown in close-up View 2). No. 3 is in a southward direction on Fifth Avenue and shows Legonaires and Junior Units aprroaching the reviesing stand. In this instance Sixty-third Street is to the
left and Central Park on the right.
About, 1925s
